The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Saturday, March 13, 2004 				 Power panel recruitments
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, March 12: The government has framed new rules for the appointment of members of the West Bengal Electricity Regulatory Commission.																								A selection committee set up by the government will appoint the members and the chairperson of the commission. The power secretary will be the convener of the selection panel.																								Power minister Mrinal Banerjee placed a bill containing the changed rules in the Assembly today. They will come into force immediately. The selection panel will invite applications from individuals or institutions to fill up the posts of members as notified by the government.
